<HEADLINE>
<P>
ON THE COVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Michael Landon takes the highway back to prime-time TV in "Where Pigeons Go to 
Die," a new movie airing Monday at 9 p.m. on NBC (Channels 4, 36 and 39). 
</P>
<P>
In the two-hour film, the former "Highway to Heaven" star plays 50-year-old 
Hugh Baudoum, who wistfully recalls the relationship he shared as a youngster 
with his grandfather (Art Carney). At the same time, Hugh must decide whether 
to sell his late "Da's" house. 
</P>
<P>
Robert Hy Gorman plays Hugh as a 10-year-old boy who once trained homing 
pigeons and learned about the value of home in the process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, COLOR, (cover) Michael Landon, Art Carney star in "Where Do Pideons Go 
To Die". 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
