<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAUREEN O'CONNOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Please don't use your valuable and limited space to cover such peripheral 
topics. 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles also continues to suffer the same civic ills set forth: 
homelessness, choked roads, aging library and sewer systems, undermanned police 
force, drug- and gang-related troubles, trash-disposal crisis and multiple 
airports, each crowded and dangerous. (None, in all honesty, as much as San 
Diego's.) 
</P>
<P>
The "Maureen" article was up to your usual good standards; please direct that 
same attention and skill to topics closer to home. 
</P>
<P>
MICHAEL YOUNGER, Toluca Lake 
</P>
</TEXT>
