<HEADLINE>
<P>
OUTTAKES: TOMBSTONE TERRITORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By From Pat H. Broeske 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The resurrection of Jim Morrison continues: The late lead singer of the Doors, 
who'll be the subject of a soon-to-shoot film directed by Oliver Stone, is 
currently the subject of a decidedly offbeat video tribute by German singer 
Nina Hagen. 
</P>
<P>
The video -- yet to be issued here -- opens at Morrison's Paris gravesite, 
where a Morrison look-alike with angel's wings is perched on the gravestone. 
</P>
<P>
Nina appears from a cluster of fans to take a heavenly phone call -- Mahalia 
Jackson requesting that Nina sing the gospel tune "Hold Me." Nina protests, 
"But I'm a white chick." Mahalia talks her into it. 
</P>
<P>
The rest of the video finds Nina dancing and singing through Paris streets, 
doing "Hold Me" rock 'n' roll style. 
</P>
<P>
For PolyGram's Mercury label, it's a cut from an album titled "Nina Hagen," 
available domestically only as an import. From Pat H. Broeske 
</P>
</TEXT>
