<HEADLINE>
<P>
CURRENTS: A GUIDE TO THE BEST OF SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA; 
</P>
<P>
KIDS; 
</P>
<P>
A CLOSE CRAWL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KAY DIEHL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
REACHING INTO AN assortment of pillowcases and wicker baskets, the Lizard Lady 
performs birthday magic: She keeps a party of 5-year-olds spellbound for an 
hour. Her traveling reptile repertoire includes Alana the Iguana, various 
skinks and snakes, and Bob the Tortoise, who may attempt to escape with all 
deliberate speed. 
</P>
<P>
A preschool teacher during the week, Melanie Bishop knows how to talk to kids, 
providing a running commentary on reptile habits. All of the children are 
allowed to touch her pets, but only the birthday child gets the privilege of 
holding them. 
</P>
<P>
But lest some of the young party guests feel left out, the Lizard Lady has one 
more surprise for the grand finale: Her name is Sheila, and she's an 8-foot 
python. Unlike the Lizard Lady's other reptiles, Sheila can be "worn" by one or 
more giggly kids (and adults). 
</P>
<P>
 Party rates are $125 and up. The Lizard Lady can be reached at (818) 781-8367. 
(818) 
</P>
<P>
KAY DIEHL 
</P>
</TEXT>
