<P>
SECRET INGREDIENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In response to "The Revenge of Successful Sitcoms," Jan. 14, by Steve 
Weinstein: 
</P>
<P>
Regarding TV producer Bob Boyett's comment that he and partner Tom Miller "want 
a certain amount of nurturing people, a certain amount of women and older 
people (on their sitcom staffs)," may I suggest that in his next interview he 
refrain from referring to women and people over 35 as some kind of secret 
ingredient in their sitcom stew. 
</P>
<P>
Instead of coming across as the open-minded, family-loving fellows they claim 
to be, Boyett and Miller sure sound like just another pair of sexist, ageist 
Hollywood producers to me. 
</P>
