<HEADLINE>
<P>
JOHN WAYNE AIRPORT, AVIATOR EDDIE MARTIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In 1974 Supervisor Thomas F. Riley was appointed to the Orange County Board of 
Supervisors for the 5th District, which happens to have an airport within its 
boundaries. Since his first day on the job, Riley has been deeply involved in 
both making the airport a good neighbor and meeting the vital needs of air 
transportation. 
</P>
<P>
Supervisor Riley's leadership made the settlement agreement with the city of 
Newport a reality. This action permitted the current needed improvements at the 
airport. In short, he has truly earned the recognition suggested in our letter 
to the county board that would name the new terminal at John Wayne Airport the 
Thomas F. Riley Terminal. 
</P>
<P>
Some have said the terminal should bear the name of aviation pioneer Eddie 
Martin because his contributions to aviation in the county are well known. The 
present terminal was named The Eddie Martin Terminal in 1989, and will be used 
for general aviation activities upon opening of the new terminal. General 
aviation, of course, was and is Eddie's first love and this recognition seems 
appropriate. Contrary to rumors, the Eddie Martin Terminal is not slated for 
demolition. 
</P>
<P>
Both of these men deserve a place in the history of air transportation in 
Orange County and we believe the recognition suggested would properly honor 
Thomas F. Riley for his many years of dedication to the improvement of aviation 
services in Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
EUGENE H. MORIARTY 
</P>
<P>
President 
</P>
<P>
Orange County Aviation Council 
</P>
