<HEADLINE>
<P>
WALNUT VALLEY SUPERINTENDENT TO RETIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The superintendent of the Walnut Valley Unified School District announced he 
will retire Dec. 31. 
</P>
<P>
David L. Brown has headed the Walnut school district since 1972. During his 
tenure, the district grew from 5,000 to 12,000 students. 
</P>
<P>
The board of trustees said it will begin a search for Brown's replacement this 
spring. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
