<HEADLINE>
<P>
61 ARRESTED AT ANTI-ABORTION RALLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
San Diego police Saturday arrested 61 anti-abortion demonstrators who tried to 
block the office of a Hillcrest physician. 
</P>
<P>
All of those arrested were expected to be released pending court dates. 
</P>
<P>
All were to be charged with misdemeanor violations, including trespassing, 
failing to disperse for police officers and resisting arrest at the 
demonstration site on Fourth Avenue, just north of downtown. 
</P>
<P>
Police said there were no serious injuries. 
</P>
<P>
Six of those arrested complained of bruised wrists and paramedics were 
summoned, said police spokesman David Cohen. 
</P>
<P>
No police officers were injured, Cohen said. 
</P>
<P>
The demonstrators were members of Operation Rescue, a nationwide anti-abortion 
group that dramatizes its cause by trying to shut down family planning centers 
and physicians who provide family planning services. 
</P>
</TEXT>
