<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORKER HURT WHEN HE FALLS INTO PLANT BOILER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A construction worker at a Santa Clarita power plant suffered serious head and 
neck injuries when he fell 25 feet into an empty boiler Saturday morning. 
</P>
<P>
Gordon McBrayer, 34, was lifted out of the four-foot-wide hole in the boiler 
with a crane and then flown by helicopter to Henry Mayo Newhall Memorial 
Hospital, said Howard Spinrad, a Los Angeles County firefighter. 
</P>
<P>
McBrayer fell about 6:30 a.m., shortly after the end of his shift at the AES 
Placerita co-generation power plant. He lay there for about 10 to 15 minutes 
until a co-worker noticed he was missing and heard his moans. 
</P>
<P>
McBrayer was still conscious when rescuers pulled him out, Spinrad said. He was 
in serious condition Saturday night, a hospital spokeswoman said. 
</P>
