<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRUDENTIAL PLANS 'LIVING PAYOUTS' TO TERMINALLY ILL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Prudential Insurance Co. said Friday it will make so-called "living payouts" to 
life insurance policyholders who are terminally ill or permanently confined to 
a nursing home to help ease their last months. 
</P>
<P>
Prudential, based in Newark, N.J., said the benefit option will be available on 
current policies having death benefits of at least $25,000 and on new policies 
of at least $50,000. 
</P>
<P>
The option will be offered at no additional cost, the insurer said. 
</P>
