<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN DIES AFTER POLICE CHASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
San Diego County Sheriff's homicide officers are investigating the case of an 
unidentified man who collapsed and died Friday after being arrested by San 
Diego police officers. 
</P>
<P>
The identity of the victim -- a black male in his mid-20s -- remained unknown 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
An autopsy was expected to be performed. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego police placed the man in custody shortly before 3 p.m. Friday after a 
short chase on foot in Southeast San Diego, according to accounts provided by 
the sheriff's and police departments. He was arrested on suspicion of burglary, 
possession of stolen property and possession of drug paraphernalia, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Shortly after being arrested, police said, the man collapsed for unknown 
reasons and was rushed to Paradise Valley Hospital in National City. He was 
pronounced dead at 9:19 p.m., the coroner's office said. 
</P>
