<TEXT>
<P>
Richard Eder finds "depressing" and "complacent" (H. L.) Mencken's note to 
himself that "there is no other Jew in Baltimore who seems suitable" for the 
Maryland Club (Book Review, Jan. 14). 
</P>
<P>
As a curmudgeonly Jew, I see the remark as exquisite sarcasm. 
</P>
<P>
M. L. WHITMORE 
