<HEADLINE>
<P>
CURRENT PAPERBACKS: EVERGLADES BY CONNIE TOOPS; 
</P>
<P>
THE SKY ISLANDS OF SOUTHEAST ARIZONA BY KATE CROWLEY &amp; MIKE LINK (VOYAGEUR: 
$14.95 EACH, ILLUSTRATED) 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two new installments in Voyageur's "Wilderness" series devoted to America's 
indigenous flora and fauna. 
</P>
<P>
Mike Link's descriptions of the animals and people who inhabit the Arizona 
deserts and riparian environments have a crisp clarity lacking in the other 
writers' work. Connie Toops' personal accounts of trekking through the forests 
and swamps of the Everglades really don't tell the reader much about that 
fragile, threatened environment. But most people will buy these large-format 
books for the gorgeous color photographs of egrets, cacti, sunsets, etc. that 
make both volumes resemble outsize Sierra Club calendars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
