CSUN VOLLEYBALL TEAM PLACES 6TH IN SANTA BARBARA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Long Beach State defeated Cal State Northridge, 6-15, 15-13, 15-10, Saturday 
for fifth place in the UC Santa Barbara Invitational men's volleyball 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
It was the third match of the day and seventh in two days for Northridge, which 
earlier defeated UCLA, ranked second in NCAA Division I, and the University of 
Manitoba, the top-ranked Canadian collegiate team. The Matadors finished the 
tournament 5-2. 
</P>
<P>
"We played great all weekend," CSUN Coach John Price said. "It really showed 
that we're right there at the top. We can compete with the best teams in the 
country." 
</P>
<P>
Three freshmen -- Gary Reznick of Taft High, Coley Kyman of Reseda, and Ken 
Lynch of Crespi -- started for Northridge. 
