<TEXT>
<P>
Meldrick Taylor cleared the last obstacle for his March 17 junior welterweight 
title unification bout against Julio Cesar Chavez by stopping Ramon Flores in 
one round in Atlantic City, N. J. 
</P>
<P>
Taylor (24-0-1), the International Boxing Federation champion, knocked Flores 
down twice with a left hook. Although Flores (21-7-1) rose on three for both 
knockdowns, referee Ted Pick halted the bout. 
