COLLEGE GUARD MAKES 15 THREE-POINTERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PORTSMOUTH, Ohio 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Shawnee State's Joe Smith made 15 three-point field baskets while scoring 58 
points in a 118-84 victory Saturday night over Wilmington College. 
</P>
<P>
Smith, a 6-foot-2 senior guard, hit 21 of 31 shots, including 15 of 24 
three-point attempts and his only free throw. 
