<HEADLINE>
<P>
BIG WEST ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
NEW MEXICO ST. BEATS UTAH ST. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Keith Hill scored 18 points and Michael New added 10 and grabbed 12 rebounds as 
New Mexico State defeated Utah State, 81-73, in a Big West Conference game 
Saturday night in Logan, Utah. 
</P>
<P>
Utah State (11-9, 5-4) held a 51-47 lead with 14:27 left, but Hill paced New 
Mexico State's comeback by scoring seven points during a 14-8 run. 
</P>
<P>
His two free throws with 3:39 left gave New Mexico State (17-2, 8-1) a 71-69 
lead. 
</P>
<P>
Pacific 56, Fresno St. 53 -- Don Lyttle and Anthony Woods scored 17 points 
apiece to lead the Tigers at Stockton. 
</P>
<P>
Pacific (11-7, 4-5) held a 12-point lead midway through the second half but 
were ahead by just two with a minute remaining. Lyttle scored a field goal with 
54 seconds left, and Woods hit two free throws with 22 seconds to go and UOP 
had a safe 56-50 lead. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story; Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA012890-0172 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 168454 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
January 28, 1990, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 23; Column 1; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
