<HEADLINE>
<P>
SNEAKS '90: FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Last Sunday, Calendar published its annual "Sneaks" issue, this year with a 
list of the "423 (or so) movies" scheduled for release during 1990. 
</P>
<P>
Some additions, clarifications and corrections: 
</P>
<P>
Three Columbia Pictures releases, "Revenge," "Blind Fury" and "Loose Cannons," 
will all be released in the next month or so, not at the end of the year as was 
reported. 
</P>
<P>
"Revenge," produced by Hunt Lowry and Stanley Rubin, not by Ray Stark, will 
open Feb. 16. It is a Columbia/Rastar production). 
</P>
<P>
"Late for Dinner" (fall ) -- Mark Andrus is the screenwriter, not director W.D. 
Richter. 
</P>
<P>
"Home Grown" (unscheduled) -- This E.K. Gaylord II/Martin Poll production is 
directed by Stuart Rosenberg, not Stuart Benjamin. 
</P>
<P>
"Queen's Logic" (summer) -- Tony Spiridakis wrote the script, not director 
Steve Rash. 
</P>
