<HEADLINE>
<P>
DRAMATIC DIFFERENCE AT SOUTH COAST REPERTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Rick Vanderknyff 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Across the street from the Pacific Symphony's performing space at the Orange 
County Performing Arts Center is South Coast Repertory, the county's other 
main, home-grown arts organization. Its reputation exceeds the Pacific 
Symphony's -- the theater received a Tony Award in 1988 -- yet ticket prices 
there for main-stage productions appear to be in line with other regional 
theater companies around the country. 
</P>
<P>
Tickets for the current, acclaimed production of Howard Korder's "Search and 
Destroy" run $21 to $28. Prices for main-stage productions at the La Jolla 
Playhouse last season ran $18 to $25 (prices for the upcoming season have yet 
to be announced). At the Goodman Theatre in Chicago, tickets for the current 
production of "The Winter's Tale" are $18 to $29. 
</P>
<P>
At the Gem Theatre in Garden Grove, tickets for the current production of 
"Twelfth Night" are $16 to $20. Rick Vanderknyff 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Sidebar 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
TICKETS; PRICES; ARTS -- ORANGE COUNTY; SOUTH COAST REPERTORY; THEATER 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
