<HEADLINE>
<P>
$900 RAISED FOR TOT LEFT BEHIND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HUNTINGTON BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
About $900 has been raised by employees at Bob's Big Boy restaurants around 
Orange County for the 21-month-old daughter of a waitress killed Jan. 5. 
</P>
<P>
Organizers collected the last of the donations last week, said Elliot Sousa, 
manager at the Huntington Beach Big Boy where Tammy Davis, 19, worked as a 
waitress before being shot just minutes after getting off work. The suspect in 
the case is Brian Keith Framstead, Davis' former boyfriend and father of their 
daughter. 
</P>
<P>
Half the $900 will go toward savings bonds for the child, while the other half 
was given to Davis' grandmother, who is taking care of the girl. SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
